commit_message: Merge pull request #100 from zauberlabs/master Client: timeouts are configurable

Client: timeouts are configurable The read/connection timeout that are hardcoded at 60s are now
configurable as each environment where the library works has their own
threshold of the time acceptable to wait.

Merge pull request #92 from iron-io/size-overflow Fix total_messages overflow for well-used queue

Represent queue size and total_messages as long There were cases of total_messages being above max int. I also adjusted
queue size just in case, even though it should be much less common.

I didn't create another QueueModel constructor overload since I don't see
the reason for public constructors on that class to begin with. Same deal with
QueueModel.setSize.

Write messages directly to HTTP request stream ...instead of creating a string, which was causing tons of allocations.

Don't allocate new Gsons all the time We can reuse the same one. The documentation says that this is safe,
even in the face of multiple threads.

Use StringBuilder instead of StringBuffer StringBuilder should almost always be preferred to StringBuffer
since it's unsynchronized.

(This isn't too critical to performance, but I noticed it while looking
around.)
